          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I calculate 20% off a price?</summary>
            <p>Multiply the price by 0.80 (1 − 0.20). For example, 20% off £50 = £50 × 0.80 = £40. You save £10.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How do I find the original price before discount?</summary>
            <p>Divide the sale price by (1 − discount/100). For example, if £80 is after a 20% discount, the original price was £80 ÷ 0.80 = £100.</p>
          </details>
